Class ReservationManager

  • Object
    • ReservationManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ReservationManager
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Manages the Reservation of the Restaurant by keeping track of list of reseration and a counter to help ensure the uniqueness of the id of reservation.
    Author:
    Kenrick

    • Field Detail

      • reservations

        private Vector<Reservation> reservations
        List of reservations, implemented in Vector data structure. Each entry consists of a reference to existing Reservation object.

      • idCounter

        private int idCounter
        Identifier (id) counter of the reservations, used to assign a unique id for new reservation. The value is one more than the size of reservations vector.

      • BUFFER_TIME

        private static final int BUFFER_TIME
        Buffer time (in minutes) for Reservation to expire from its dateTime. If BUFFER_TIME minutes have passed and no order has been made from that reserved table, then the reservation is set to be expired.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Method Detail

      • createReservation

        public int createReservation(Customer customer,
                    Calendar dateTime,
                    Table table)
        Creates new Reservation for a specified Customer on a specified dateTime for an allocated Table.

        This method checks if the given parameter dateTime is valid by comparing it to the current time. It is valid if the reservation is made for a future time.

        Next, the method creates a new Reservation object with incremental id and store it to the reservation list (reservations).

        Finally, it returns the identified (id) of the newly created Reservation object.

        Parameters:
        customer - Customer object containing details of who made the reservation
        dateTime - Calendar object representing date and time for reservation
        table - Table object representing table that will be allocated for the reservation, should be obtained from TableManager.allocateTable(int). checkExpiry() must be called before calling TableManager.allocateTable(int)!
        Returns:
        identifier (id) of Reservation that is created here.

      • getReservationById

        private Reservation getReservationById(int reservationId)
        Traverses through the reservation list to return the Reservation object with the specified identifier (id). Returns null if not found.
        Parameters:
        reservationId - the identified (id) of a reservation
        Returns:
        Reservation object with the specified identifier (id); null if not found.

      • getReservationByTableId

        public Reservation getReservationByTableId(int tableId,
                                  String status)
        Returns a Reservation object that being allocated to a specified table with a specified reservation status by traversing the reservaton list. Returns null if not found.

        This method is being used to get Customer.membership when OrderInvoice.printInvoice() is called

        Parameters:
        tableId - id of a table (table number).
        status - status of the reservation.
        Returns:
        Reservation object that being allocated to a specified table with a specified reservation status; null if not found.

      • checkReservation

        public int checkReservation(int reservationId)
        Checks the current reservation by first checking the expiration of all reservations (by calling checkExpiry) and then gets the Reservation object by its id (by calling getReservationById). Finally prints the Reservation object (by calling Reservation.printReservation())

        Returns 1 on successful printing, -1 otherwise

        Parameters:
        reservationId - Identifier (id) of a reservation to be checked.
        Returns:
        1 on successful printing, -1 otherwise

      • checkExpiry

        public void checkExpiry()
        Calls checkExpiry(Reservation) for every Reservation object stored in reservation list (reservations)

      • checkExpiry

        public void checkExpiry(Reservation reservation)
        Checks the expiration of the specified Reservation object. If the current time exceeds the reservation time plus the buffer time, then sets the reservation status to be "Expired".
        Parameters:
        reservation - Reservation object to be checked.

      • cancelReservation

        public int cancelReservation(int reservationId)
        Cancels the reservation of the specified identified (id) by first getting the specified reservation object and then sets the status to "Cancelled" if the current status is "active" Returns 1 on successful cancellation, -1 otherwise.
        Parameters:
        reservationId - identifier (id) of the reservation.
        Returns:
        1 on successful cancellation, -1 otherwise.
